EmailTemplate.name: HSC and IB subject selection evening
EmailTemplate.subject: HSC and IB Subject Selection Evening: 5.30pm, Tuesday 31 July
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
In the coming weeks Year 10 students will begin to make important and exciting decisions that plan a course of study for Year 11 and 12, leading to the award of either the Higher School Certificate or International Baccalaureate Diploma.
The pattern of study they choose will reflect their needs, interests, passions, strengths, and future career aspirations. It is important that students make a fully informed choice.
To facilitate this, I invite you to join us for a Subject Selection Information Evening on Tuesday 31 July. The evening will begin at 5.30pm in the Cathedral and will provide students and parents with the opportunity to meet with Senior Staff and Leaders of Learning to gain information and advice that will help students make decisions regarding their pattern of study for 2019.
If you would like to attend the evening, please let me know by return email at bperry@sacs.nsw.edu.au.
A Handbook which outlines course structure requirements for HSC and IB and includes detailed information on the range of subjects on offer, will be available early in Term 3. Further details regarding the Subject Selection Information Evening will also be availalble at that time.
I hope you can join us for this information evening as we support Year 10 students through the important decision-making process.
Regards
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
St Andrew's Cathedral School
Sydney Square, Sydney NSW 2000, Australia direct +61 2 9286 9507 mobile 0418 255 923 email BPerry@sacs.nsw.edu.au phone +61 2 9286 9500 fax +61 29286 9550
You are receiving this invitation as you have previously indicated interest in enrolment at St Andrews Cathedral School. You are most welcome to come join us for subject selection, however, if you would like to unsubscribe from further invitations, please click here.
